                    <div class="col-lg-12">
                        <h4>When you consider that effectively engaging the workforce will result in people getting "up to speed" faster and performing at a higher rate, you can start to see why the Human Resources function is really more of A <span>PROFIT CENTER</span> than anything else (e.g. a necessary evil?) </h4>
                        <h4>Optimizing the workforce will deliver real money to the organization, but it takes someone applying the science and art (and probably a software tool . . .  )  for the results to follow.</h4>
                        <h4>We'd like for you to think of us as your partners in your Workforce Optimization efforts.  We bring <span>"advice and tools"</span> that are designed and intended to help you <span>"cultivate employee talent."</span></h4>
                        <h4>Workforce Optimization is less of a revolution and more of an evolution  (although thinking of it as a "revolution" does appeal to us . . .  )   At its core, Workforce Optimization is the HR strategy of taking a holistic view across all of the factors that enhance or inhibit employee performance. </h4>
                    </div>
