                        <h3 class="lead text-center">Someone has said that Workforce Optimization is like Talent Development on steroids. We think that's a pretty good analogy!</h3>
                        <h4>Any good HR professional will tell you that helping employees perform requires more than just hiring the right person.  It also requires, training them, having a good manager guide and lead them, and paying them according to the marketplace and their contribution.  and that is just the starting point of the list . . .</h4>
                    </div>
